<p>
    The <code>eval()</code> function evaluates or executes an argument.
    If the argument is an expression, <code>eval()</code> evaluates the expression.
    If the argument is one or more JavaScript statements, <code>eval()</code> executes the statements.
</p>

<div class="text-center m3">
    <button class="btn btn-info" onclick="EvalTest()">Eval Test</button>
</div>

<div class="card text-white bg-info m-3 col-3">
